The '''Alliance of the Presidential Majority''' ({{lang-fr|Alliance pour la majorité présidentielle}}, AMP) is a [[political alliance]] formed by supporters of [[President of the Democratic Republic of the Congo|President-elect]] [[Joseph Kabila]] following the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo general election, 2006|2006 general elections]] in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lephareonline.net/acte-constitutif-de-lalliance-de-la-majorite-presidentielle-restructuree/|title=Acte constitutif de l'Alliance de la Majorité Présidentielle restructurée - Journal Le Phare, Quotidien indépendant paraissant à Kinshasa|last=lephare|date=2010-05-26|work=Journal Le Phare, Quotidien indépendant paraissant à Kinshasa|access-date=2017-04-22|language=fr-FR}}</ref> This bloc currently holds the majority of seats in the [[National Assembly (Democratic Republic of the Congo)|National Assembly]] with 332 out of 500 seats.
On 3 October 2018 the [[Unified Lumumbist Party]] and its parliamentary allies exited the coalition in anticipation of the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo general election, 2018|2018 general elections]].<ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.mediacongo.net/article-actualite-42970_palu_majorite_le_divorce_est_consomme.html| title = PALU-Majorité : le divorce est consommé !| date = 3 October 2018| website = mediacongo.net| publisher = Media Congo Press| access-date = 3 October 2018| language = French}}</ref>
