{{Infobox song | name = Amazing | cover = | alt = | type = single | artist = [[Tatjana Mihhailova|Tanja]] | album = | released = 10 January 2014 | format = [[Music download|Digital download]] | recorded = 2013 | studio = | venue = | genre = [[Pop music|Pop]] | length = 3:00 | label = | writer = Timo Vendt, Tatjana Mihhailova | producer = | prev_title = | prev_year = | next_title = | next_year = | misc = {{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Estonia}} "Amazing" | image = [[File:ESC2014 - Estonia 01.jpg|230px]] | caption = Tanja performing the song during the first dress rehearsal of the first semi-final of the Eurovision Song Contest 2014 | year = 2014 | country = Estonia | artist = [[Tatjana Mihhailova|Tanja]] | language = English | languages = | composer = Timo Vendt, Tatjana Mihhailova | lyricist = Timo Vendt, Tatjana Mihhailova | place = | points = | lyrics = | prev = Et uus saaks alguse | prev_link = Et uus saaks alguse | next = Goodbye to Yesterday | next_link = Goodbye to Yesterday (Elina Born & Stig Rästa song) |place_semi = 12th |points_semi = 36 }} }} [[File:Tanja - Amazing presentation (English).webm|thumb|250px|Video of [[Tanja Mihhailova|Tanja]] presenting the song.]]
'''"Amazing"''' is a song by [[Russians in Estonia|Russian-Estonian]] singer [[Tanja Mihhailova-Saar|Tanja]]. It was chosen to represent [[Estonia]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2014]] in [[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]].<ref name="Estonia">{{cite web|title=Estonia sends Tanja to Copenhagen!|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=estonia_sends_tanja_to_copenhagen|last=Storvik-Green|first=Simon|work=Eurovision.tv|accessdate=1 March 2014|date=1 March 2014}}</ref> The song competed in the first semi-final on 6 May 2014, where it was performed third, following [[Latvia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2014|Latvia]]'s [[Aarzemnieki]] with "[[Cake to Bake]]" and preceding Sweden's [[Sanna Nielsen]] with "[[Undo (Sanna Nielsen song)|Undo]]".<ref>{{cite web|last=Siim|first=Jarmo|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=running_order_for_eurovision_semi-finals_decided|title=Running order for Eurovision Semi-Finals decided|date=24 March 2014|accessdate=26 March 2014|work=Eurovision.tv}}</ref> It failed to reach the final.
Along with Tanja, there were three backing singers (Marilin Kongo, [[Kaire Vilgats]] and Marvi Vallaste) and one dancer (Argo Liik) on stage.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esckaz.com/2014/est.htm|title=ESCKAZ - Eurovision 2014 - Tanja (Estonia)|date=4 April 2014|accessdate=14 April 2014|work=ESCKaz}}</ref>
