{{Infobox flag |Name = Yerevan |Article = |Image = Flag of Yerevan.jpg |Nickname = Yerevan flag |Morenicks = |Use = |Symbol = |Proportion = |Adoption = September 27, 2004 |Design = Yerevan Arms surrounded by twelve red triangles on white background |Type = Capital }}
The '''flag of [[Yerevan]]''' shows Yerevan's arms surrounded by 12 triangles, symbolizing 12 past capitals of [[Armenia]] on a white background, symbolizing clearness and simplicity. The colors used in the flag are the same as in the flag of [[Armenia]], representing the importance of [[Yerevan]] as capital.
The flag final design was approved on September 27, 2004.<ref>[http://www.yerevan.am/main.php?lang=1&page_id=114 Official website of Yerevan Municipality]</ref>
