{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} '''Hatzi-''' or '''Chatzi-''' ({{lang-el|Χατζη-}}) is a [[Prefix (linguistics)|prefix]] of [[Greece|Greek]] family names. It derives ultimately from the Arabic ''[[Hajji]]'', denoting one who has successfully completed a [[pilgrimage]].
In Christianity, the prefix is added when someone had committed the pilgrimage to Jerusalem. For example, if the surname was Stefanou, the name would then be Hatzistefanou after the journey. ==See also== * [[Hatzis]] * [[Hadžić]] * [[Hatzianestis]] * [[Hatzidakis]] * [[Hatzimichalis]]
