{{Politics of Suriname}}
The [[districts of Suriname|ten districts]] of [[Suriname]] are divided into 62 '''resorts''' ([[Dutch language|Dutch]]: ''ressorten''). Within the capital city of [[Paramaribo]], a resort entails a neighbourhood, in other cases it is more akin to a municipality, consisting of a central place with a few settlements around it. The resorts in the [[Sipaliwini District]] are especially large, since the inlands of Suriname are sparsely inhabited.
The average resort is about 2600&nbsp;km² and has almost 8,000 inhabitants. According to article 161 of the [[Constitution of Suriname]], the highest political body of the resort is the [[resort council]]. Elections for the resort council are held every five years and are usually at the same time as the [[Suriname general election]]s.
